Readme: 10E-DP-ST-2117-1a-VC-6-JSON-2020-04-06(Nonlinear Upsamplers Data).json
This json file contains arrays of strings and individual string scalars, each string representing the exponent,
sign and mantisssa of an exact number in binary (i.e. a binary number with terminating fractional part).
The value of a member, named crcSets, crcReference or crcFeatureDeconvolution, of an object listed below, is the
crc-16-ccitt checksum, using initial data 65535, of all strings in arrays and all scalar strings corresponding to
other members of the same object in their order of appearance in the object, concatenating arrays in row-major
order as they are listed and coding the concatenation in utf-8.  These checksums are metadata for verifying the
integrity of this file, which is their only purpose.
The number of mantissa binary digits is 19, but the first mantissa binary digit, 1, is implicit.
Each string contains five characters.  The second character is a + or -.  The other four characters
are taken from from a base 64 alphabet where A-Z represent 0-25, a-z represent 26-51, 0-9 represent 52-61,
- (minus) represents 62 and _ (underscore) represents 63.
The sign is given by the second character.
Where the first character is A, the real number is 0.
If the first character is A, the sign must be +, the final three characters must be AAA and the exponent, sign
and mantissa are not defined.
Where the first character is not A, the exponent is represented by an offset-32 code comprising the first
character of the string.  The exponent ranges from -31 (B) to +31 (underscore).
Where the first character is not A, the mantissa is 1 + u/64 + v/64*64 + w/64*64*64, where u, v and w are the
values represented by the third, fourth and fifth characters of the string.
